# Coding Standards

## Overview

This document captures the coding standards and patterns for CreatorOSX. Currently, there are **no ESLint or Prettier configurations**, so these standards are based on observed patterns in the existing codebase and the project's user rules.

---

## Code Style

### Formatting

**Indentation:**

- ✅ Use **2 spaces** (not tabs)
- ✅ Consistent throughout JSX and TypeScript

**Quotes:**

- ✅ Single quotes for JSX attributes: `className='text-blue-500'`
- ✅ Double quotes for TypeScript strings: `const name = "Creator OSX"`
- ✅ Template literals for multi-line or interpolation: `` `Hello ${name}` ``

**Semicolons:**

- ✅ Use semicolons consistently
- ✅ All statements should end with semicolons

**Line Length:**

- ✅ Target: ~80-100 characters
- ✅ Break long Tailwind class strings into multiple lines when needed

**Example:**

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC = () => {
  const title = "My Title";

  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-4 px-6 py-4">
      <span className="text-sm font-medium">{title}</span>
    </div>
  );
};
```

