## React Patterns

### Component Declaration

**Standard Pattern:**

```typescript
// ✅ Named export with React.FC
export const ComponentName: React.FC = () => {
  return <div>Content</div>;
};

// ✅ With props
export const ComponentName: React.FC<Props> = ({ prop1, prop2 }) => {
  return <div>{prop1}</div>;
};
```

**Avoid:**

```typescript
// ❌ Default exports (harder to refactor)
export default function ComponentName() {}

// ❌ Missing type annotation
export const ComponentName = () => {};
```

### Component Organization

**File Structure:**

```typescript
// 1. Imports (React first, then libraries, then local)
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { Icon } from "lucide-react";
import { Button } from "./ui/Button";

// 2. Types/Interfaces
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
}

// 3. Constants/Data (if component-specific)
const DEFAULT_TITLE = "Default";

// 4. Sub-components (if tightly coupled)
const SubComponent = () => <div />;

// 5. Main component
export const MainComponent: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ title }) => {
  // Hooks first
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);

  // Helper functions
  const handleClick = () => {};

  // Early returns
  if (!title) return null;

  // Main render
  return <div>{title}</div>;
};
```

### Props Destructuring

**Preferred:**

```typescript
// ✅ Destructure in function signature
export const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({ title, description, children }) => {
  return <div>{title}</div>;
};

// ✅ Default values in destructuring
export const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({
  title,
  variant = "default",
  size = "md",
}) => {
  return <div>{title}</div>;
};
```

### State Management

**Local State:**

```typescript
// ✅ Use useState for UI state
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState("home");

// ✅ Descriptive names
const [mobileMenuOpen, setMobileMenuOpen] = useState(false);
```

**State Updates:**

```typescript
// ✅ Direct updates for simple state
setIsOpen(!isOpen);

// ✅ Functional updates for state based on previous
setCount((prev) => prev + 1);
```

**No Global State Yet:** When needed, use Zustand (per project rules)

