## Component Patterns

### Single Responsibility

**Rule:** Each component should do one thing well

```typescript
// ✅ Good - focused component
export const PricingCard: React.FC<PricingProps> = ({ price, features }) => {
  return (
    <div className="card">
      <h3>${price}</h3>
      <ul>
        {features.map((f) => (
          <li>{f}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
};

// ❌ Bad - too many responsibilities
export const PricingSection: React.FC = () => {
  // Handles data fetching, formatting, rendering, analytics...
  // Should be split into smaller components
};
```

### Component Size

**Target:** < 400 lines per file (project rule)

**Action:** Refactor when approaching 300+ lines

- Extract sub-components
- Move helper functions to utils
- Split into multiple related components

### Reusability

**UI Components Pattern:**

```typescript
// ✅ Variant-based design
interface ButtonProps {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
}

export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({
  variant = "primary",
  size = "md",
  className = "",
  children,
  ...props
}) => {
  const baseStyles = "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full";
  const variants = {
    primary: "bg-slate-900 text-white",
    outline: "border border-slate-200 bg-white",
    // ...
  };

  return (
    <button
      className={`${baseStyles} ${variants[variant]} ${className}`}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

### Props Spreading

**Use Case:** Passing through native element props

```typescript
// ✅ Good - allows all button props
interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: "primary" | "outline";
}

export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({
  variant = "primary",
  className = "",
  ...props // Captures onClick, disabled, type, etc.
}) => {
  return <button className={`btn ${className}`} {...props} />;
};

// Usage:
<Button onClick={handleClick} disabled={isLoading} type="submit">
  Submit
</Button>;
```

